               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Tuzuk-i Timuri by Salar Muhammad son of La'l Muhammad
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_98-item1">
                     <author key="person_f3607">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">Salar Muhammad son of La'l Muhammad</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9560">Tuzuk-i Timuri.</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" key="work_9560">The Institutes of Timur.</title>
                     <note>Second flyleaf, recto: declaration of Ghulam Muhammad dated 4 Sha'ban 1239 recording his gift of the book to 'Ali Sahib at Sikandrabad, attested by four witnesses. Final folio, verso: a plan of a battle formation, such as is found in the text, but laid out on ruled pencilled lines, with the units shown in the European fashion as blocks with flags on. Headings punctuation and vocalisation in red, largely confined to the opening and closing pages. Text consists of The Institutes of Timur.</note>
                     <incipit>Tuzuk u kankash-i umur-i mulk-giri u jahandari</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, i, pp. 280-3.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Rieu, i, pp. 177-8.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Ethe, No 196.</bibl>
                        <bibl>For Newbold's gift see Donations Register for March 19 1842 and J.R.A.S. vii (1843), Proceedings, p. xxxi. For Thomas John Newbold see Buckland)</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
